As person who bakes some of the time I hate running to the store cause I forgot what I need. Luckily though, theirs substations and work around for ingredients that you dont have.


♡If you don't have cake flour♥
1 Cup ~ All purpose flour
2 tablespoons ~ cornstarch
-----------------------------------------------------------------
♡If you don't have Almond Flour♥
Basically you'll have to pulse regular almonds in a food processor until you reach a flour-like consistency👍
-----------------------------------------------------------------
♡If you don't have food Coloring♥
for this they ask for yellow and Orange
▶Yellow (add water to the spice)
Turmeric powder
saffron flowers


▶Orange (add water to the spice)
carrots
paprika
can also use sweet potato


Note: 
if you want your food coloring to be thick then make a slurry
bring the food coloring to a boil.
grab a 1/2 cup cornstarch and 1/2 cup of water. mix in together, not with the food coloring
pour the mix with  he food coloring until you reach desired thickness. turn off heat and refrigerate til cool.

I made it using agar powder, since I saw some people asking if you can use agar, I will share some advice for the substitions since I failed to do the recipe correctly when adding agar instead of gelatin sheet at first.

When you mix the cheese, the cream, the yogurt, the vanilla and the lemon juice, do it in a pot in low heat, in the order that Hidamari uses in the video. When it is about to boil, add the agar powder and don't stop mixing gently (don't use high heat! Be patient and let it boil in low heat). Leave it in the fire two more minutes mixing non stop and then let it cool just a bit, then put it in the mold and into the fridge. I employed 2g of agar but it can vary from mark to mark.

Then, the second step when doing the transparent layer, boil the water plus sugar and lemon but only boil the first half of the amount indicated and add another 2g of agar (I added less the first time and it didn't solidify). Pour it, refrigerate at least 30' as Hidamari said and then boil the rest of the water-sugar-lemon mix and add another 2g of agar. Pour it and let it rest (I waited a whole night).

It was my first time using agar and it finally went well! Thanks again for the recipe

I tried it. I expected a lot so I was a little disappointed, even if it is still good. What disappointed me was the absence of the taste of oreo.
I will do this recipe again but with a few modifications: I will add a tiny bit of cocoa powder (to slightly reinforce the taste of chocolate) and I will add a little sugar (very slightly) to enhance the taste a little.
I will not dip the cooked churros in cinnamon sugar either: it removes the taste of oreo even more and the sugar does not stick to the churros. Maybe I'll wait for them to cool and sprinkle with icing sugar ...

(I used google translation)

Je l'ai essayé. Je m'attendais à beaucoup donc j'ai été un peu déçu, même si ça reste quand même bon. Ce qui m'a déçu c'est l'absence du goût d'oreo.
Je referai cette recette mais en faisant quelques modifications : je rajouterai un tout petit peu de poudre de cacao (pour renforcer légèrement le goût de chocolat) et je metterai un peu de sucre (très légèrement) pour relever un peu le goût.
Je ne tremperai pas non plus les churros cuits dans du sucre à la cannelle : ça éloigne encore plus le goût d'oreo et le sucre ne colle pas aux churros. Peut-être que j'attendrai qu'ils refroidissent et saupoudrai de sucre glace...

Je suis (et restera) une abonnée de cette chaîne. Ce n'est pas du tout une critique mais plus une alternative pour ceux qui n'ont pas été conquis par la recette d'origine. Je trouve cette chaîne très inspirante !

For anyone who doesn't have a scale, I tried the recipe and it's DELICIOUS. here's what I used: 
1.5 medium eggs
4 tbsp sugar
1/3 tsp salt
2.15 tsp honey 
3/4 unsalted butter stick
5 tbsp whole milk
3/4 cake flour
1 tsp baking powder
2 round tbsp cocoa powder
3.5 tbsp almond powder 
Chocolate chips 
*you can make cake flour by filling a a cup of all propose flourthen taking out 2 tbsp of it and replace it with 2 tbsp corn starch then sift twice. After that measure the amount you need and save the rest.
* I didn't have almond powder so I putpeeled almonds in a food processor for a few seconds (too much time will turn it to paste) then sift it.

1.  Gently loosen the unsalted butter, add sugar, whip thoroughly, add egg yolk and vanilla extract and mix.  2 .  Add milk at room temperature and mix, sift through the flour and baking powder.  3.  Whip the egg white, and when a large bubble rises, divide the sugar into 3 and whip it to form a meringue with soft horns, and divide it into the dough 3 times and mix.  4 .  Divide the dough into 3 pieces, add cocoa powder in one place and dark cocoa powder in the other, and mix to make two different types of chocolate dough. 5.  Put the thick chocolate dough in the mold, flatten it, put the light chocolate dough on it, flatten it, pour the vanilla dough, flatten it, and bake it for 45-50 minutes in a 170-degree preheated oven.

The ingredients:
1. 3 slices of bread 
2. 30gr butter 
3. 20gr chopped garlic(around 2/2,5 tablespoon, depends on ur taste)
5. 10gr(less than 1 tablespoon) honey(or any sweetness) 
6. Parsley or oregano 
Mix them well, put on the bread. Put some butter or oil on the pan n stir fry till it gets golden brown. Done.

Does anyone know if there's another way of knowing when to stop heating the yolk mixture? I have quite some experience in baking, but I don't have a thermometer ☹️

This might be late but to help anyone who read this: If you don't have thermometer to check on the temp, just dip your finger into the mixture! It should be lukewarm temp like, just slightly warm (not hot!) and you're good to go. The heating (40°) is there to help you dissolve the sugar (especially when you use coarser sugar) and to rise the eggs mixture quicker when you mix it.

I hope this helps and good luck! 💕

*자세한 레시피 설명은 유튜브 자막 기능을 켜서 확인해주세요~
탐스러운 체리가 들어 있는 체리 생크림 케이크를 만들었어요~
체리를 작게 잘라 끓여 과육은 크림에 넣고 과즙은 글레이즈에 넣어 만들었는데 색이 예쁜 것 같아요~
크림에 체리가 들어 있어 체리 향과 살짝 씹히는 체리 과육이 정말 맛있더라구요~
그냥 생크림 케이크 보다 과일을 넣은 생크림 케이크가 저는 훨씬 맛있고 풍미가 좋아 선호하는 편이에요~
생 과일을 크림에 넣으면 물이 생길 수 있어 끓여 넣으면 과일 본연의 맛을 즐길 수 있으면서 모양도 잘 유지할 수 있는 것 같아요~
앙증맞은 체리를 올려 장식하니 심플하면서도 포인트가 되더라구요~
장식에 사용한 잎사귀는 집에 있는 커피나무의 잎사귀를 씻어 장식했어요~

Hi everyone! As soon as I saw this recipe I just had to try out and went grocery shopping to buy everything I needed. And I’ll just say a couple things to this recipe. - If you don’t have white food coloring it’s fine. Just red food coloring works as well. - you should definitely use baking powder or your cake will turn out very flat and thin.!!! - you might need more heavy cream and sugar than the recipe tells you. For me it definitely wasn’t enough and I couldn’t cover up the top like in the video. Therefore you’d need more cherries too.. I can’t say how the cake tastes yet since it’s in the fridge but I’m really looking forward to try it out.✨🍒

Super delicious cake recipe ....

1.  Place a bowl of eggs on a pot of hot water, add sugar, honey, and vanilla extract, stir and mix until the temperature reaches 40 degrees.  2 .  Whip until a rich ivory-colored foam is obtained with a hand mixer, then sift through the flour and mix.  3.  Put a little bit of the dough in a bowl of melted unsalted butter and milk (temperature 50 to 60 degrees), mix, put in the main dough, mix, and transfer about a third of the dough to another bowl.  |  4 .  Mix the mixed dough with strawberry powder + warm milk and pink and white food coloring. Mix the other dough with cocoa powder + warm milk.  5.  Pour two pieces of dough into the mold, flatten it, and bake and cool for 30 minutes in an oven preheated to 170 degrees.
 6.  Cut the top, bottom, and edges of the cooled sheet and prepare it by cutting into a long rectangular shape.  7.  Add strawberry jam to cream cheese, mix fresh cream and mix to make cream.  8 .  Apply the cream between the chocolate and strawberry sheets alternately, and stack 2 times.  9.  Cut off both ends, apply the cream evenly over the ground, and set for 30 minutes in the freezer.  10.  Pour ganache of about 28 to 30 degrees onto the cake and coat it.

I tried this at home, took about 5 hours (cleanup is included in that time) :) 
Heres the American instructions:
-4 eggs
-1 tsp of vanilla extract
-1/4 a cup of sugar
-1/4 tsp of salt
-3 & 1/2 cups of cake flour (I couldn't find cake flour at Hyvee so I made my own: Pour out 3 & 1/2 cups of all-purpose flour into a  bowl, remove 7 tablespoons and add 7 tablespoons of cornstarch. Whisk together, then sift 5 times. I learned when sifting, to our bowl of flour into a sieve owner a Large bowl or the flour will escape, than pour that flour back into the small bowl, than pour over sieve into large bowl again.)
-2 cups of milk
-5 tablespoons of unsalted butter (so a bit over half a stick)
-Red and white food coloring
-2 cups of Heavy cream 
-1/3 a cup of strawberry jam
-Cooking oil (for pan)

Suggestion: For the heart mold, I suggest getting one from the store and not using a cookie cutter or than you will spend a long time on a cake and only have a tiny cake :( get one that's about 6 inches across and 3 inches high)

-Meringue

-Filling

1/8 cup of condensed milk
